Class Specialty

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.model.Specialty
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public final class Specialty
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    Represents a surgical specialty, with the associated calcuation variables.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.

    • Field Detail

      • SPECIALTY_NAME_MAX

        public static final int SPECIALTY_NAME_MAX
        The maximum length of a valid surgical specialty: 100. VistA surgical specialties are 40 characters or less, but we support more in case we want to add a suffix (e.g., two different cardiac models).

      • getName

        public final java.lang.String getName()
        The display name of the specialty. Will be no longer than SPECIALTY_NAME_MAX characters. This name is mutable but should be unique (i.e., no other Specialty should have the same name).

      • setName
